>
> c =3D readknob();  /* or whatever the cmd is for reading it */
>
> if ( c < 64 )
> {
>   print "a";
> }
> else if ( c < 128 )
> {
>   print "b";
> }
> else if ( c < 192 )
> {
>   print "c";
> }
> else
> {
>   print "d";
> }
>
> or set a variable inside each if block and then run through a switch
> statement later when you're doing your printing.
